Using APT with PPA Repository:
Add the WebUpd8 PPA repository:


sudo add-apt-repository ppa:nilarimogard/webupd8
Install Curseradio:


sudo apt install curseradio
Directly from GitHub Repository:
Clone the GitHub repository:

git clone https://github.com/chronitis/curseradio.git
Navigate into the cloned directory:

cd curseradio
Run the setup script:


python3 setup.py install
Install Dependencies:
Ensure that Python 3 and the required libraries (requests, xdg, and lxml) are installed. You can install them using pip:


pip install requests xdg lxml
Users should follow these steps based on their preference, and make sure to address any dependencies before running the setup script. This information is helpful for users who want to install Curseradio on their Linux systems.
